### Perform a basic query with Claude Agent SDK (TypeScript)

Source: https://context7.com/anthropics/claude-agent-sdk-typescript/llms.txt

Demonstrates how to initiate a basic conversation with a Claude agent using the `query` function. It sends a text prompt and iterates through the streaming response, logging assistant messages and session initialization details like session ID and available skills.

```typescript
import { query } from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";

// Basic query with Claude
const response = query({
  prompt: "Help me analyze this codebase and suggest improvements",
  options: {
    model: "claude-sonnet-4-5"
  }
});

for await (const message of response) {
  if (message.type === 'assistant') {
    console.log(message.content);
  } else if (message.type === 'system' && message.subtype === 'init') {
    console.log(`Session ID: ${message.session_id}`);
    console.log(`Available skills: ${message.skills?.join(', ') || 'none'}`);
  }
}
```

