### Extract User Data with Zod Schema Validation

Source: https://context7.com/anthropics/claude-agent-sdk-typescript/llms.txt

Defines a Zod schema for user objects with nested metadata and requests structured output from Claude to extract validated user information. The response is parsed as a typed object matching the schema definition with optional metadata fields.

```typescript
import { query } from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";
import { z } from "zod";

// Define a schema for structured output
const UserSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string(),
  email: z.string().email(),
  age: z.number().int().positive(),
  role: z.enum(["admin", "user", "guest"]),
  metadata: z.object({
    lastLogin: z.string().datetime(),
    preferences: z.array(z.string())
  }).optional()
});

// Request structured output
const response = query({
  prompt: "Extract user information from the database configuration file",
  options: {
    model: "claude-sonnet-4-5",
    workingDirectory: "/path/to/project",
    structuredOutput: {
      schema: UserSchema,
      name: "user_data"
    }
  }
});

for await (const message of response) {
  if (message.type === 'structured_output') {
    // Validated data matching UserSchema
    const userData = message.data;
    console.log('User:', userData.name);
    console.log('Email:', userData.email);
    console.log('Role:', userData.role);
  }
}
```
